<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 1:51PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Meagher and northeastern Gallatin Counties through 215 PM MDT...
At 151 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 23
miles east of Toston, or 28 miles south of White Sulphur Springs,
moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ringling.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
